@node "HOWTO" "How to play."

@{bg fill}@{fg highlight}The Menu:@{fg text}@{bg background}

Use arrow-keys or joystick in port2 to select item.
Use enter-key or Joystick button to activate item.

The menu is divided into five parts.

@{fg fill}The first:@{fg text}
"Start Game"  -Goto next menu part.
"Credits"     -Shows who made this game.
"Exit"        -quits the game.

@{fg fill}The second and third:@{fg text}
Here you select your craft.

@{fg fill}The fourth:@{fg text}
Here you select how many times to win on each battleground.
After each battleground you will be asked if you want to
play another round.

@{fg fill}The fifth:@{fg text}
Here you select a battleground.


@{bg fill}@{fg highlight}In the game:@{fg text}@{bg background}

First of all, player one might hit [J] or [K] to change between
joystick in port1 and keyboard control. Keyboard is default.
That's because otherwise the mouse would piss you off real easy.

@{fg fill}The keys for player one are:@{fg text}

   @{b}Up:@{ub} [Q]
 @{b}Down:@{ub} [A]
 @{b}Left:@{ub} [Z]
@{b}Right:@{ub} [X]
 @{b}Fire:@{ub} [Space]

There are no conflicts with these keys, so there's no reason to
change them. Hahaha.

@{fg fill}And for player two:@{fg text}

The arrow-keys and [Enter], or the joystick in port2.
There's no need for player two to change between joystick and
keyboard, they work simultaneously.

@{fg fill}Other keys:@{fg text}

[P] pauses the game.
[Esc] Quits the game.

@endnode

