@NODE "POWERUPS" "Goodies"

@{bg fill}@{fg highlight}Power-ups:@{fg text}@{bg background}

When you take a power-up, a countdown starts. You can see it
in the status-bar. When the countdown reaches zero, the effect
of the power-up will go away.


@{fg fill}Faster sight:@{fg text}
This power-up increases the speed with which your sight (the
little white dot) rotates around your saucer. It can be very good
if your opponent's driving a slow saucer.
Just fly around your opponent in circles and shoot. Your
opponent's sight won't be fast enough, so he won't be able to hit
you. The symbol in the status bar for this one is a yellow little
this with a black S on.

@{fg fill}Speed increase:@{fg text}
This one simply increases your saucer's speed.
The symbol is a "speedy" red S.

@{fg fill}Super bounce:@{fg text}
This mean little thing makes your saucer bounce more when you hit
a wall. Can be very frustrating some times.
The symbol for this one is a tiny little saucer with four arrows
around.

@{fg fill}Gravity:@{fg text}
This power-up adds some gravity to your opponent's saucer.
Very frustrating - for him!
Symbol: A little saucer with an arrow under.

@{fg fill}Med-kit:@{fg text}
This one is not like the other power-ups. It simply gives you some
more energy. It's not controlled by any timer, and it's got it's
own box too.

@{fg fill}Inverted controls:@{fg text}
Haha! If you take this one, your opponent's controls will be inverted!
I.e. if he pulls his joystick to the right, he'll go to the left.
Muahaha.


@{bg fill}@{fg highlight}Weapons:@{fg text}@{bg background}

@{fg fill}First grade:@{fg text}
This is the standard ammo that you have when you start at a
battleground. You have an unlimited number of these, so don't be
affraid of running out of them.

@{fg fill}Second grade:@{fg text}
These green shots are a bit more powerful than the red ones.
A bit bigger too. But you can only get them by taking one of the
little animating green things popping up here and there in the game.

@{fg fill}Third grade:@{fg text}
Wooha! Be careful with these! You can only get them by finding them.
If you see a yellow animating little circle, go for it!
These shots are BIG, and really deadly. But you only get 20 of them
for every yellow thing you take.

@ENDNODE
